title: Algebraic Complexity Theory
venue: Handbook of Theoretical Computer Science, Volume A: Algorithms and Complexity

tldr.text: This chapter discusses algebraic complexity theory, which unites two quite different traditions, that of straight-line program or arithmetic circuit or computation sequence and that of computation tree.
